	<a name="IDX_BIOGRAPHY"></a>
        <div class="section separator"><hr /></div>
    
        <div class="rte">
                <h6>Education</h6>
                <p>PhD, MSc (University of Toronto)<br />
 BSc, Honours Physics (Concordia University)</p>
                <h6>Research interests</h6>
                <p>I am a High Energy Theorist and I work in the general area of Electroweak Theory/Beyond The Standard Model phenomenology.<br />
<br />
My main areas of interest in research are:<br />
<ol>
<li>Supersymmetry, Minimal Supersymmetric Standard Model and Beyond, with particular emphasis on the Left-Right Supersymmetric Model.</li>
<li>Precision Tests of Physics Beyond the Standard Model, especially CP violation and Flavor Violation (lepton flavor violation, electric dipole moments, top FCNC decays).</li>
<li>Spontaneous symmetry violation (in particular the connection between R parity and CP)</li>
<li>LHC phenomenology: Higgs, and top production and decays, extra gauge bosons, exotic particles.</li></ol><br />
I collaborate with high energy theorists in Montreal, Chicago, Helsinki, Taiwan and the Tata Institute.</p>
        </div>
    
    
    

    
        
            <a name="IDX_PUBLICATION"></a>
            <div class="section separator"><hr /></div>
        
            <h2 class="section-header">Recent publications</h2>
        
            <div class="rte">
                    <p><ol>
<li>T. M. Aliev, Mariana Frank and Ismail Turan, &quot;Collider Effects ofUnparticle Interactions in Multiphoton Signals&quot;, Phys. Rev. D 80, 1140191-18 ( 2009).</li>
<li>Durmus A. Demir, Mariana Frank, Dilip Gosh, Katri Huitu, SantoshKumar Rai and Ismail Turan, &quot;Doubly Charged Higgsinos at Tevatron&quot;,Phys. Rev. D 79, 095006 1-10 ( 2009).</li>
<li>Ahmed Ali, Durmus A. Demir, Mariana Frank and Ismail Turan,&quot;Search for Gauge Extensions of the MSSM at the LHC&quot;, Phys. Rev. D79, 095001 1-32 ( 2009).</li>
<li>Mariana Frank, Nasser Saad and Ismail Turan, &quot;The Casimir Force inRandall Sundrum Models with q 1 dimensions&quot;, Phys. Rev. D 78, 0550141-19 (2008).</li>
<li>Durmus A. Demir, Mariana Frank, Katri Huitu, Santosh Kumar Raiand Ismail Turan, &quot;Signals of Doubly-Charged Higgsinos at the CERN LargeHadron Collider&quot;, Phys. Rev. D 78, 035013 1- 13 (2008).</li>
<li>Mariana Frank, Ismail Turan and Ismet Yurdusen, &quot;The Integrability ofPauli System in Lorentz Violating Background&quot;, JHEP01, 039, 1-20 (2008).</li>
<li>Mariana Frank, Katri Huitu and Santosh Kumar Rai,&quot;Doubly ChargedHiggsino Production and Decays in e-e- colliders&quot;, Phys. Rev. D 77, 0150061- 16 (2008).</li></ol>For a complete list of papers published while at Concordia see <a href="http://inspirehep.net/" target="_blank">Spires List</a>.<br />
<br /></p>
